abstract: Democrats have one, too, and impeached the president on it.
snippet: Democrats have one, too, and impeached the president on it.
lead_paragraph: President Trump’s impeachment is the result of a conspiracy theory. Democrats and other supporters of the charges against Mr. Trump might be reluctant to accept that labeling. But a conspiracy theory is not necessarily crackpot or wrong: If the conspiracy is real, the theory may be correct.

abstract: More than 8 million people have signed up for coverage next year under former President Barack Obama's health care law, the government said Friday,  a sign of continued demand for the program amid persistent uncertainty over its future.
snippet: More than 8 million people have signed up for coverage next year under former President Barack Obama's health care law, the government said Friday,  a sign of continued demand for the program amid persistent uncertainty over its future.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — More than 8 million people have signed up for coverage next year under former President Barack Obama's health care law, the government said Friday, a sign of continued demand for the program amid persistent uncertainty over its future.
headline_main: Obamacare Sign-Ups Steady as Debate Persists Over Its Future
headline_print_headline: Obamacare Sign-Ups Steady as Debate Persists Over Its Future

abstract: An investigation concluded that the Treasury Department’s top spokeswoman did not commit research misconduct, but required extensive revisions.
snippet: An investigation concluded that the Treasury Department’s top spokeswoman did not commit research misconduct, but required extensive revisions.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Monica Crowley, the Treasury Department’s assistant secretary for public affairs, committed “localized instances of plagiarism” in her 2000 Ph.D. dissertation, Columbia University found in an investigation that ultimately concluded she did not commit research misconduct.

abstract: Minnesota Sen. Amy Klobuchar has argued for weeks that Pete Buttigieg, the mayor of a small Indiana city, doesn't have enough experience to be a serious contender for the Democratic nomination for president. As she heads into a 27-county tour  of Iowa, the lead-off caucus state, s he's seeing some payoff for bringing those frustrations  fully into public view.
snippet: Minnesota Sen. Amy Klobuchar has argued for weeks that Pete Buttigieg, the mayor of a small Indiana city, doesn't have enough experience to be a serious contender for the Democratic nomination for president. As she heads into a 27-county tour  of ...
lead_paragraph: CENTERVILLE, Iowa — Minnesota Sen. Amy Klobuchar has argued for weeks that Pete Buttigieg, the mayor of a small Indiana city, doesn't have enough experience to be a serious contender for the Democratic nomination for president. As she heads into a 27-county tour of Iowa, the lead-off caucus state, s he's seeing some payoff for bringing those frustrations fully into public view.
headline_main: Klobuchar Steps Up Hits on Buttigieg With Iowa Vote Looming
headline_print_headline: Klobuchar Steps Up Hits on Buttigieg With Iowa Vote Looming

abstract: The Democratic National Committee is again upping its polling and fundraising requirements for presidential hopefuls to qualify for participating in the campaign's seventh debate in January, the first in a series of four held in the earliest-voting states.
snippet: The Democratic National Committee is again upping its polling and fundraising requirements for presidential hopefuls to qualify for participating in the campaign's seventh debate in January, the first in a series of four held in the earliest-votin...
lead_paragraph: COLUMBIA, S.C. — The Democratic National Committee is again upping its polling and fundraising requirements for presidential hopefuls to qualify for participating in the campaign's seventh debate in January, the first in a series of four held in the earliest-voting states.
headline_main: Party Again Ups Stakes for 7th Democratic Candidate Debate
headline_print_headline: Party Again Ups Stakes for 7th Democratic Candidate Debate

abstract: Readers in the United States with ties to Iran share how they have been affected by President Trump’s travel ban.
snippet: Readers in the United States with ties to Iran share how they have been affected by President Trump’s travel ban.
lead_paragraph: With the holidays and a long school break almost here and many families gathering together, we reached out to those who have been affected by President Trump’s travel ban to see how they and their relatives are managing.

abstract: U.S. Chief Justice John Roberts is poised to serve a highly visible though largely ceremonial role in the Senate impeachment trial of President Donald Trump due next month. But it is in his day job on the Supreme Court that the mild-mannered jurist could have a bigger impact on Trump's presidency.

abstract: U.S. lawmakers who control the fate of President Donald Trump left Washington for a holiday break on Friday with no agreement over how they will handle the Senate trial to consider his impeachment charges in January.

abstract: U.S. presidential candidate Michael Bloomberg has spent more on campaign ads in the last few weeks than his main Democratic rivals have all year. Yet his level of support has barely risen, according to a Reuters/Ipsos poll.
snippet: U.S. presidential candidate Michael Bloomberg has spent more on campaign ads in the last few weeks than his main Democratic rivals have all year. Yet his level of support has barely risen, according to a Reuters/Ipsos poll.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON/NEW YORK — U.S. presidential candidate Michael Bloomberg has spent more on campaign ads in the last few weeks than his main Democratic rivals have all year. Yet his level of support has barely risen, according to a Reuters/Ipsos poll.
headline_main: What Does Millions in Ad Spending Get You? So Far for Bloomberg, a Few Points
headline_print_headline: What Does Millions in Ad Spending Get You? So Far for Bloomberg, a Few Points
